Year 355 (&lt;a href="Roman%20numerals"&gt;CCCLV&lt;/a&gt;) was a &lt;a href="common%20year%20starting%20on%20Sunday"&gt;common year starting on Sunday&lt;/a&gt; (link will display the full calendar) of the &lt;a href="Julian%20calendar"&gt;Julian calendar&lt;/a&gt;. At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Arbitio and Maesius (or, less frequently, year 1108 "&lt;a href="Ab%20urbe%20condita"&gt;Ab urbe condita&lt;/a&gt;"). The denomination 355 for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the &lt;a href="Anno%20Domini"&gt;Anno Domini&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="calendar%20era"&gt;calendar era&lt;/a&gt; became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.
